"http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/writing/lod/1",{"ana":52},"#text_condition.incomplete",{"lettering":54,"dimensions":55},"Crudely carved plain lunate letters, fairly regular in size. Lunate epsilon and sigma, with use of ligature in line 1.",[56,64,69,75],{"type":57,"l":58,"from":59,"to":59,"h":60,"unit":61,"atLeast":62,"atMost":63},"letterHeight","Line 1","line1","19-20","mm","19","20",{"type":57,"l":65,"from":66,"to":66,"h":67,"unit":61,"atLeast":68,"atMost":62},"Line 2","line2","17-19","17",{"type":70,"l":71,"from":59,"to":66,"h":72,"unit":61,"atLeast":73,"atMost":74},"interlinear","Interlineation line 1 to 2","5-10","5","10",{"type":70,"l":76,"from":66,"to":77,"h":72,"unit":61,"atLeast":73,"atMost":74},"Interlineation line 2 to 3","line3",{"_":79,"notBefore":80,"notAfter":81},"1st — 3rd century CE",1,300,[83,88],{"_":84,"type":85,"ref":86,"region":87},"Centuripae","ancient","http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/462153","Sicilia",{"_":89,"type":90,"ref":91,"region":87},"Centuripe","modern","http://sws.geonames.org/2525032",[93],[94,95],37.62336,14.74049,{"_":97,"type":98,"subtype":99,"notAfter":100,"geo":17},"One of 8 epigraphic fragments acquired from Centuripe by the museum, 19 February 1914 (and Orsi was unable to confirm more precisely the locale in which they were found). Currently in storage, magazzino B, cassette 13","found","discovered","1914",[],{"_":103,"type":104,"subtype":105,"resp":106,"xml:id":107,"geo":17},"Prag  2014-09","observed","autopsied","#JP","autopsy",[109,116],{"n":110,"url":111,"height":112,"width":113,"desc":114,"surfaceType":115},"screen","ISic001854_tiled.tif","2027px","3198px","I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2014-09-11","front",{"n":110,"url":117,"height":118,"width":119,"desc":114,"surfaceType":120},"ISic001854_rear_tiled.tif","1805px","2934px","rear","Sicily","Siracusa",{"_":124,"role":125,"ref":126,"museum":127},"Museo Archeologico Regionale Paolo Orsi","museum","http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/museum/097",{"slug":128,"type":125,"name":124,"uri":126,"description":129,"location":130},"097","An outstanding collection of archaeological material. The collection ranges from Siracusa and the surrounding territory (Megara Hyblaia, Akrai, Kasmenai etc) to encompass all of eastern Sicily, reaching as far as Gela and Agrigento. The ground floor covers prehistory through to the end of the Classical period. Upstairs includes Hellenistic and Roman Syracuse and a display of material from the catacombs. A gallery displaying material from Hellenistic eastern Sicily is in preparation.",{"settlement":122,"region":122,"country":131,"address":132,"geo":133},"Italy","Viale Teocrito 66, 96100 - Siracusa",{"lat":134,"lon":135},37.07636989,15.2866213,{"_":137,"type":138},"34735a","inventory",{"_":140,"mainLang":141,"languages":142},"Ancient Greek","grc",[140],{"type":144,"bibl":145},"edition",[146],{"type":147,"n":148,"author":149,"title":150,"date":151,"citedRange":152,"ptr":153,"ref":154,"inscriptionDate":155,"citation":156,"uri":157,"year":158},"bulletin","NSA","","Notizie degli scavi di antichità","1876-","231",{"target":154},"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/4MCP2PVV","1915","\u003Cspan>Accademia nazionale dei Lincei, Istituto nazionale di archeologia e storia dell’arte (Italy), e Reale Accademia d’Italia, «Notizie degli scavi di antichità», \u003Ci>Notizie degli Scavi di Antichità\u003C/i>, 1876, \u003Ca href=\"http://www.worldcat.org/oclc/1646037\">http://www.worldcat.org/oclc/1646037\u003C/a>\u003C/span>","https://www.zotero.org/groups/isicily/items/4MCP2PVV","1876",{"type":160,"bibl":161},"discussion",[17],{"editor":163,"principal":165,"contributors":166,"change":170},{"_":164,"ref":106},"Jonathan Prag",{"_":164,"ref":106},[167],{"_":164,"xml:id":168,"ref":169},"JP","http://orcid.org/0000-0003-3819-8537",{"_":171,"when":172,"who":106},"Jonathan Prag created file from autopsy","2025-08-12",{"n":110,"url":111,"height":112,"width":113,"desc":114,"surfaceType":115},[175,178,180,183],{"atLeast":176,"atMost":177},19,20,{"atLeast":179,"atMost":176},17,{"atLeast":181,"atMost":182},5,10,{"atLeast":181,"atMost":182},[185],"Notizie degli scavi di antichità, 1876-",[187],"4MCP2PVV",[189,190,191,19,24,28,192,193,194,195,196,197,198,141],"isic001854","fragmentary epitaph",{"_":5},"centuripae","centuripe","sicilia","sicily","siracusa","museo archeologico regionale paolo orsi","ancient greek",[],{"title":201,"body":202,"divs":203,"editions":228,"images":238,"handnote":249},"ISic001854. Fragmentary epitaph","\u003Cdiv id=\"editions\">\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Jonathan Prag; edition source: autopsy Prag 2014-09\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-interpretive\" lang=\"grc\">  \u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"σι\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"σι\">\u003Cspan data-text=\"σι\">σι\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/span> χρ\u003Cspan class=\"petraeligature\" title=\"Ligature: these characters are joined\">η͡σ\u003C/span>-\u003Cbr id=\"al2-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>τέ χρε \u003Cbr id=\"al3-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>[ἔ]ζ̣η̣σ̣ε̣ς̣ \u003Cbr id=\"al4-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">l.2 reg., orig. χρε\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Jonathan Prag; edition source: autopsy Prag 2014-09\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-diplomatic\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\">\u003Ca id=\"al1-diplomatic\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"σι\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"σι\">\u003Cspan data-text=\"σι\">ΣΙ\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/span>ΧΡ\u003Cspan class=\"petraeligature\" title=\"Ligature: these characters are joined\">Η͡Σ\u003C/span>\u003Cbr id=\"al2-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>ΤΕΧΡΕ\u003Cbr id=\"al3-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>[...].....\u003Cbr id=\"al4-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">l.2 reg., orig. χρε\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"facsimile-images\">\u003Ch2>Facsimile Images\u003C/h2>\u003Ca href=\"ISic001854_tiled.tif\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2014-09-11\" src=\"ISic001854_tiled-thumb.tif\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic001854.jpg\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2014-09-11\" src=\"ISic001854-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic001854_rear_tiled.tif\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2014-09-11\" src=\"ISic001854_rear_tiled-thumb.tif\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic001854_rear.jpg\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2014-09-11\" src=\"ISic001854_rear-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"apparatus\">\u003Ch4>Apparatus criticus\u003C/h4>\u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan>\u003Cspan>text from autopsy\u003C/span>\u003C/span>; \u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"2\">2: \u003Cspan>Orsi: ΣΧΕΡΕ\u003C/span>\u003C/span>; \u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"2\">\u003Cspan>Orsi: ........\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>\u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"translation\">\u003Ch2>English translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">\u003Ca href=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0003-3819-8537\">Jonathan Prag\u003C/a>\u003C/p>  \u003Cp>Farewell, worthy [---]sis, you lived [----].\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"commentary\">\u003Ch2>commentary\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>Although recording the tops of the letters of line 3 in the inventory, in the published edition in NSA 1915, Orsi declined to print anything for the final line, but the traces are clearly compatible with \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">ἔζησες\u003C/span>. The faint marginal guideline on the right side, and the spacing / vacat at the end of lines 2 and 3 suggests that the right margin of the lettering may be preserved (the use of ligature in line 1 might further support that theory). However, if that is so, then there appears only to be c.2 letters missing from the left side, which makes restoring the name in line 1 difficult: presumably one of the handful of very short names ending in -σις, of which the most common in Sicily is Σῶσις. The form χρε for χαῖρε is rare in Sicily (see \u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic004073\" target=\"_blank\">ISic004073\u003C/a> from Lipara).\u003C/p>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"bibliography\">\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli> Orsi NSA 1915 231 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001392\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001392\u003C/a>  \u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003C/div>  \u003Cdiv id=\"handnote\">\u003Cp>Crudely carved plain lunate letters, fairly regular in size. Lunate epsilon and sigma, with use of ligature in line 1.\u003C/p> Line 1  19-20  Line 2  17-19  Interlineation line 1 to 2  5-10  Interlineation line 2 to 3  5-10  \u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"license\"> Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence. \u003C/div>",[204,207,210,213,216,219,222,225],{"id":205,"html":206},"editions","\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Jonathan Prag; edition source: autopsy Prag 2014-09\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-interpretive\" lang=\"grc\">  \u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"σι\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"σι\">\u003Cspan data-text=\"σι\">σι\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/span> χρ\u003Cspan class=\"petraeligature\" title=\"Ligature: these characters are joined\">η͡σ\u003C/span>-\u003Cbr id=\"al2-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>τέ χρε \u003Cbr id=\"al3-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>[ἔ]ζ̣η̣σ̣ε̣ς̣ \u003Cbr id=\"al4-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">l.2 reg., orig. χρε\u003C/p>\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Jonathan Prag; edition source: autopsy Prag 2014-09\u003C/div>\u003Cdiv id=\"edition-diplomatic\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\">\u003Ca id=\"al1-diplomatic\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"σι\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"σι\">\u003Cspan data-text=\"σι\">ΣΙ\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/span>ΧΡ\u003Cspan class=\"petraeligature\" title=\"Ligature: these characters are joined\">Η͡Σ\u003C/span>\u003Cbr id=\"al2-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>ΤΕΧΡΕ\u003Cbr id=\"al3-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>[...].....\u003Cbr id=\"al4-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">l.2 reg., orig. χρε\u003C/p>\u003C/div>",{"id":208,"html":209},"facsimile-images","\u003Ch2>Facsimile Images\u003C/h2>\u003Ca href=\"ISic001854_tiled.tif\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2014-09-11\" src=\"ISic001854_tiled-thumb.tif\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic001854.jpg\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2014-09-11\" src=\"ISic001854-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic001854_rear_tiled.tif\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2014-09-11\" src=\"ISic001854_rear_tiled-thumb.tif\">\u003C/a>\u003Ca href=\"ISic001854_rear.jpg\">\u003Cimg title=\"I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2014-09-11\" src=\"ISic001854_rear-thumb.jpg\">\u003C/a>",{"id":211,"html":212},"apparatus","\u003Ch4>Apparatus criticus\u003C/h4>\u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan>\u003Cspan>text from autopsy\u003C/span>\u003C/span>; \u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"2\">2: \u003Cspan>Orsi: ΣΧΕΡΕ\u003C/span>\u003C/span>; \u003C/li>\u003Cli>\u003Cspan class=\"2\">\u003Cspan>Orsi: ........\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>",{"id":214,"html":215},"translation","\u003Ch2>English translation\u003C/h2>\u003Cp class=\"translation-author\">\u003Ca href=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0003-3819-8537\">Jonathan Prag\u003C/a>\u003C/p>  \u003Cp>Farewell, worthy [---]sis, you lived [----].\u003C/p>  ",{"id":217,"html":218},"commentary","\u003Ch2>commentary\u003C/h2>  \u003Cp>Although recording the tops of the letters of line 3 in the inventory, in the published edition in NSA 1915, Orsi declined to print anything for the final line, but the traces are clearly compatible with \u003Cspan class=\"lang\" lang=\"grc\">ἔζησες\u003C/span>. The faint marginal guideline on the right side, and the spacing / vacat at the end of lines 2 and 3 suggests that the right margin of the lettering may be preserved (the use of ligature in line 1 might further support that theory). However, if that is so, then there appears only to be c.2 letters missing from the left side, which makes restoring the name in line 1 difficult: presumably one of the handful of very short names ending in -σις, of which the most common in Sicily is Σῶσις. The form χρε for χαῖρε is rare in Sicily (see \u003Ca href=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic004073\" target=\"_blank\">ISic004073\u003C/a> from Lipara).\u003C/p>  ",{"id":220,"html":221},"bibliography","\u003Ch2>bibliography\u003C/h2>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli> Orsi NSA 1915 231 \u003Ca href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001392\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001392\u003C/a>  \u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  \u003Cul>\u003Cli>\u003C/li>\u003C/ul>  ",{"id":223,"html":224},"handnote","\u003Cp>Crudely carved plain lunate letters, fairly regular in size. Lunate epsilon and sigma, with use of ligature in line 1.\u003C/p> Line 1  19-20  Line 2  17-19  Interlineation line 1 to 2  5-10  Interlineation line 2 to 3  5-10  ",{"id":226,"html":227},"license"," Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence. ",[229,231,234,235],{"html":230},"Text encoding: Jonathan Prag; edition source: autopsy Prag 2014-09",{"id":232,"lang":141,"html":233},"edition-interpretive","\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  \u003Ca id=\"al1-interpretive\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"σι\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"σι\">\u003Cspan data-text=\"σι\">σι\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/span> χρ\u003Cspan class=\"petraeligature\" title=\"Ligature: these characters are joined\">η͡σ\u003C/span>-\u003Cbr id=\"al2-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>τέ χρε \u003Cbr id=\"al3-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>[ἔ]ζ̣η̣σ̣ε̣ς̣ \u003Cbr id=\"al4-interpretive\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>] \u003C/span>\u003C/div>  \u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">l.2 reg., orig. χρε\u003C/p>",{"html":230},{"id":236,"lang":141,"html":237},"edition-diplomatic","\u003Cdiv class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\">\u003Cspan class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\">\u003Ca id=\"al1-diplomatic\">\u003C!--0-->\u003C/a>\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">1\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003Cspan data-type=\"persname\" data-name-type=\"attested\" data-text=\"σι\">\u003Cspan data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"σι\">\u003Cspan data-text=\"σι\">ΣΙ\u003C/span>\u003C/span>\u003C/span>ΧΡ\u003Cspan class=\"petraeligature\" title=\"Ligature: these characters are joined\">Η͡Σ\u003C/span>\u003Cbr id=\"al2-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">2\u003C/span>ΤΕΧΡΕ\u003Cbr id=\"al3-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">3\u003C/span>[...].....\u003Cbr id=\"al4-diplomatic\">\u003Cspan class=\"linenumber\">4\u003C/span>[\u003Cspan dir=\"ltr\" class=\"gap\">---\u003C/span>]\u003C/span>\u003C/div>\u003Cp class=\"miniapp\">l.2 reg., orig. χρε\u003C/p>",[239,241,244,246],{"image":111,"thumb":240,"title":114},"ISic001854_tiled-thumb.tif",{"image":242,"thumb":243,"title":114},"ISic001854.jpg","ISic001854-thumb.jpg",{"image":117,"thumb":245,"title":114},"ISic001854_rear_tiled-thumb.tif",{"image":247,"thumb":248,"title":114},"ISic001854_rear.jpg","ISic001854_rear-thumb.jpg",[250],{"html":54},"\u003C?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>\n\u003C?xml-model href=\"https://epidoc.stoa.org/schema/latest/tei-epidoc.rng\" type=\"application/xml\" schematypens=\"http://relaxng.org/ns/structure/1.0\"?>\n\u003C?xml-model href=\"../schematron/ircyr-checking.sch\" schematypens=\"http://purl.oclc.org/dsdl/schematron\"?>\n\u003CTEI xmlns=\"http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0\" xmlns:xi=\"http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude\" xml:lang=\"en\">\n    \u003CteiHeader>\n        \u003CfileDesc>\n            \u003CtitleStmt>\n                \u003Ctitle>Fragmentary epitaph\u003C/title>\n                \u003Ceditor ref=\"#JP\">Jonathan Prag\u003C/editor>\n                \u003Cprincipal ref=\"#JP\">Jonathan Prag\u003C/principal>\n                \u003Cfunder>John Fell OUP Research Fund\u003C/funder>\n\t   \u003Cfunder>\u003Cref target=\"https://cordis.europa.eu/project/id/885040\">ERC Advanced Grant no.885040\u003C/ref>\u003C/funder>\n                \u003CrespStmt>\n                    \u003Cname xml:id=\"JP\" ref=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0003-3819-8537\">Jonathan Prag\u003C/name>\n                    \u003Cresp>original data collection and editing\u003C/resp>\n                \u003C/respStmt>\n             \u003C/titleStmt>\n            \u003CpublicationStmt>\n                \u003Cauthority>I.Sicily\u003C/authority>\n                \u003Cidno type=\"filename\">ISic001854\u003C/idno>\n                \u003Cidno type=\"TM\"/>\n                \u003Cidno type=\"EDR\"/>\n                \u003Cidno type=\"EDH\"/>\n                \u003Cidno type=\"EDCS\"/>\n                \u003Cidno type=\"PHI\"/>\n                \u003Cidno type=\"URI\">http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic001854\u003C/idno>\n                \u003Cavailability>\n                    \u003Clicence target=\"http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/\">Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence.\u003C/licence>\n                \u003C/availability>\n            \u003C/publicationStmt>\n            \u003CsourceDesc>\n                \u003CmsDesc>\n                    \u003CmsIdentifier>\n                        \u003Ccountry>Italy\u003C/country>\n                        \u003Cregion>Sicily\u003C/region>\n                        \u003Csettlement>Siracusa\u003C/settlement>\n                        \u003Crepository role=\"museum\" ref=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/museum/097\">Museo Archeologico Regionale Paolo Orsi\u003C/repository>\n                        \u003Cidno type=\"inventory\">34735a\u003C/idno>\n                        \u003C!--Adding location for old id numbers if available-->\n                        \u003CaltIdentifier>\n                            \u003Csettlement/>\n                            \u003Crepository/>\n                            \u003Cidno type=\"old\"/>\n                        \u003C/altIdentifier>\n                    \u003C/msIdentifier>\n                    \u003CmsContents>\n                        \u003CtextLang mainLang=\"grc\">Ancient Greek\u003C/textLang>\n                    \u003C/msContents>\n                    \u003CphysDesc>\n                        \u003CobjectDesc>\n                            \u003CsupportDesc>\n                                \u003Csupport>\u003Cp>A fragment of a white marble plaque, intact above, broken on the other three sides. A moulding along the upper rear edge has been chiselled off, suggesting the piece has been re-used for the inscription (rear otherwise finished smooth).\u003C/p>\n                                    \u003Cmaterial ana=\"#material.stone.marble\" ref=\"http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/material/lod/48.html\">marble\u003C/material>\n                                    \u003CobjectType ana=\"#object.plaque\" ref=\"http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/objtyp/lod/259\">plaque\u003C/objectType>\n                                    \u003Cdimensions>\n                                        \u003Cheight unit=\"cm\">6.8\u003C/height>\n                                        \u003Cwidth unit=\"cm\">12.8\u003C/width>\n                                        \u003Cdepth unit=\"cm\">1.7-2.1\u003C/depth>\n                                    \u003C/dimensions>\n                                \u003C/support>\n                                \u003Ccondition ana=\"#condition.fragment\"/>\n\t\t    \u003C/supportDesc>\n                            \u003ClayoutDesc>\n                                \u003Clayout>\u003Cp>Parts of three lines of Greek letters; guidelines also visible, observed for the first and third lines, but ignored for the second. There is a faint vertical bounding guideline on the right side.\u003C/p>\n                                    \u003Crs ana=\"#execution.chiselled\" ref=\"http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/writing/lod/1\">chiselled\u003C/rs>\n                                \t\u003Cdamage ana=\"#text_condition.incomplete\"/>\n\t\t\t\u003C/layout>\n                            \u003C/layoutDesc>\n                        \u003C/objectDesc>\n                        \u003ChandDesc>\n                            \u003ChandNote>\u003Cp>Crudely carved plain lunate letters, fairly regular in size. Lunate epsilon and sigma, with use of ligature in line 1.\u003C/p>\n                                \u003Clocus from=\"line1\" to=\"line1\">Line 1\u003C/locus>\n                                \u003Cdimensions type=\"letterHeight\">\n                                    \u003Cheight unit=\"mm\" atLeast=\"19\" atMost=\"20\">19-20\u003C/height>\n                                \u003C/dimensions>\n                                \u003Clocus from=\"line2\" to=\"line2\">Line 2\u003C/locus>\n                                \u003Cdimensions type=\"letterHeight\">\n                                    \u003Cheight unit=\"mm\" atLeast=\"17\" atMost=\"19\">17-19\u003C/height>\n                                \u003C/dimensions>\n                                \u003Clocus from=\"line1\" to=\"line2\">Interlineation line 1 to 2\u003C/locus>\n                                \u003Cdimensions type=\"interlinear\">\n                                    \u003Cheight unit=\"mm\" atLeast=\"5\" atMost=\"10\">5-10\u003C/height>\n                                \u003C/dimensions>\n                                \u003Clocus from=\"line2\" to=\"line3\">Interlineation line 2 to 3\u003C/locus>\n                                \u003Cdimensions type=\"interlinear\">\n                                    \u003Cheight unit=\"mm\" atLeast=\"5\" atMost=\"10\">5-10\u003C/height>\n                                \u003C/dimensions>\n                            \u003C/handNote>\n                        \u003C/handDesc>\n                    \u003C/physDesc>\n                    \u003Chistory>\n                        \u003Corigin>\n                            \u003CorigPlace>\u003Cregion>Sicilia\u003C/region>\n                                \u003CplaceName type=\"ancient\" ref=\"http://pleiades.stoa.org/places/462153\">Centuripae\u003C/placeName>\t\t\n                                \u003CplaceName type=\"modern\" ref=\"http://sws.geonames.org/2525032\">Centuripe\u003C/placeName>\n                            \t\u003Cgeo>37.62336, 14.74049\u003C/geo>\n\t\t\u003C/origPlace>\n                            \u003CorigDate datingMethod=\"#julian\" notBefore-custom=\"0001\" notAfter-custom=\"0300\">1st — 3rd century CE\u003C/origDate>\n                        \u003C/origin>\n                        \u003Cprovenance type=\"found\" subtype=\"discovered\" notAfter=\"1914\">One of 8 epigraphic fragments acquired from Centuripe by the museum, 19 February 1914 (and Orsi was unable to confirm more precisely the locale in which they were found). Currently in storage, magazzino B, cassette 13\u003C/provenance>\n                        \u003Cprovenance type=\"observed\" subtype=\"autopsied\" resp=\"#JP\" xml:id=\"autopsy\">Prag  2014-09\u003C/provenance>\n                        \u003Cacquisition/>\n                    \u003C/history>\n                \u003C/msDesc>\n            \u003C/sourceDesc>\n        \u003C/fileDesc>\n        \u003CencodingDesc>\n             \u003Cp>Encoded following the latest EpiDoc guidelines\u003C/p>\n             \u003Cxi:include href=\"../alists/ISicily-taxonomies.xml\">\n                 \u003Cxi:fallback>\n                     \u003Cp>Taxonomies for ISicily controlled values\u003C/p>\n                 \u003C/xi:fallback>\n             \u003C/xi:include>\n\t  \u003Cxi:include href=\"../alists/charDecl.xml\">\n\t     \u003Cxi:fallback>\n\t       \u003Cp>ISicily glyphs authority list\u003C/p>\n\t     \u003C/xi:fallback>\n\t   \u003C/xi:include>\n         \u003C/encodingDesc>\n        \u003CprofileDesc>\n            \u003CcalendarDesc>\n                \u003Ccalendar xml:id=\"julian\">\n                    \u003Cp>Julian Calendar\u003C/p>\n                \u003C/calendar>\n            \u003C/calendarDesc>\n            \u003ClangUsage>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"en\">English\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"it\">Italian\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"grc\">Ancient Greek\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"la\">Latin\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"he\">Hebrew\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"phn\">Phoenician\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"xpu\">Punic\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"osc\">Oscan\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"xly\">Elymian\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"scx\">Sikel\u003C/language>\n                \u003Clanguage ident=\"sxc\">Sikan\u003C/language>\n            \u003C/langUsage>\n            \u003CtextClass>\n                \u003Ckeywords scheme=\"http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/typeins.html\">\n                    \u003Cterm ana=\"#function.funerary\" ref=\"http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/typeins/lod/92.html\">funerary\u003C/term>\n                \u003C/keywords>\n            \u003C/textClass>\n        \u003C/profileDesc>\n        \u003CrevisionDesc status=\"edited\">\n            \u003ClistChange>\n                \u003Cchange when=\"2025-08-12\" who=\"#JP\">Jonathan Prag created file from autopsy\u003C/change>\n\t\u003C/listChange>\n        \u003C/revisionDesc>\n    \u003C/teiHeader>\n    \u003Cfacsimile>\n        \u003Csurface type=\"front\">\n            \u003Cgraphic n=\"screen\" url=\"ISic001854_tiled.tif\" height=\"2027px\" width=\"3198px\">\n                \u003Cdesc>I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2014-09-11\u003C/desc>\n            \u003C/graphic>\n            \u003Cgraphic n=\"print\" url=\"ISic001854.jpg\" height=\"2027px\" width=\"3198px\">\n                \u003Cdesc>I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2014-09-11\u003C/desc>\n            \u003C/graphic>\n         \u003C/surface>\n        \u003Csurface type=\"rear\">\n            \u003Cgraphic n=\"screen\" url=\"ISic001854_rear_tiled.tif\" height=\"1805px\" width=\"2934px\">\n                \u003Cdesc>I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2014-09-11\u003C/desc>\n            \u003C/graphic>\n            \u003Cgraphic n=\"print\" url=\"ISic001854_rear.jpg\" height=\"1805px\" width=\"2934px\">\n                \u003Cdesc>I.Sicily with the permission of the Assessorato Regionale dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana - Dipartimento dei Beni Culturali e dell’Identità Siciliana; photo J. Prag 2014-09-11\u003C/desc>\n            \u003C/graphic>\n        \u003C/surface>\n    \u003C/facsimile>\n    \u003Ctext>\n        \u003Cbody>\n            \u003Cdiv type=\"edition\" subtype=\"primary\" xml:space=\"preserve\" xml:lang=\"grc\" resp=\"#JP\" source=\"#autopsy\">\n                \u003Cab>\n                    \u003Clb n=\"1\"/>\u003Cgap reason=\"lost\" extent=\"unknown\" unit=\"character\"/>\u003CpersName type=\"attested\">\u003Cname>\u003Cw part=\"F\">σι\u003C/w>\u003C/name>\u003C/persName> χρ\u003Chi rend=\"ligature\">ησ\u003C/hi>\n                    \u003Clb n=\"2\" break=\"no\"/>τέ \u003Cchoice>\u003Corig>χρε\u003C/orig>\u003Creg>χαῖρε\u003C/reg>\u003C/choice>\n                    \u003Clb n=\"3\"/>\u003Csupplied reason=\"lost\">ἔ\u003C/supplied>\u003Cunclear>ζησες\u003C/unclear>\n                    \u003Clb n=\"4\"/>\u003Cgap reason=\"lost\" extent=\"unknown\" unit=\"character\"/>\n                 \u003C/ab>\n            \u003C/div>\n            \u003Cdiv type=\"apparatus\" resp=\"#JP\">\n                \u003ClistApp>\n                    \u003Capp>\u003Cnote>text from autopsy\u003C/note>\u003C/app>\n                    \u003Capp loc=\"2\">\u003Cnote>Orsi: ΣΧΕΡΕ\u003C/note>\u003C/app>\n                    \u003Capp loc=\"2\">\u003Cnote>Orsi: ........\u003C/note>\u003C/app>\n                \u003C/listApp>\n            \u003C/div>\n            \u003Cdiv type=\"translation\" xml:lang=\"en\" resp=\"#JP\">\n                \u003Cp>Farewell, worthy [---]sis, you lived [----].\u003C/p>\n            \u003C/div>\n            \u003Cdiv type=\"commentary\" resp=\"#JP\">\n                \u003Cp>Although recording the tops of the letters of line 3 in the inventory, in the published edition in NSA 1915, Orsi declined to print anything for the final line, but the traces are clearly compatible with \u003Cforeign xml:lang=\"grc\">ἔζησες\u003C/foreign>. The faint marginal guideline on the right side, and the spacing / vacat at the end of lines 2 and 3 suggests that the right margin of the lettering may be preserved (the use of ligature in line 1 might further support that theory). However, if that is so, then there appears only to be c.2 letters missing from the left side, which makes restoring the name in line 1 difficult: presumably one of the handful of very short names ending in -σις, of which the most common in Sicily is Σῶσις. The form χρε for χαῖρε is rare in Sicily (see \u003Cref target=\"http://sicily.classics.ox.ac.uk/inscription/ISic004073\">ISic004073\u003C/ref> from Lipara).\u003C/p>\n            \u003C/div>\n            \u003Cdiv type=\"bibliography\">\n                \u003ClistBibl type=\"edition\">\n                    \u003Cbibl type=\"bulletin\" n=\"NSA\">\n                        \u003Cauthor>Orsi\u003C/author>\n                        \u003Ctitle>NSA\u003C/title>\n                        \u003Cdate>1915\u003C/date>\n                        \u003CcitedRange>231\u003C/citedRange>\n                        \u003Cptr target=\"https://www.zotero.org/groups/382445/items/4MCP2PVV\"/>\n                        \u003Cref target=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001392\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001392\u003C/ref>\n                    \u003C/bibl>\n                   \u003C/listBibl>\n\t   \u003ClistBibl type=\"discussion\">\u003Cbibl/>\u003C/listBibl>\n            \u003C/div>\n        \u003C/body>\n    \u003C/text>\n\u003C/TEI>\n"],"uses":{"params":["slug"]}}]}
